alaa ali alewi i wa born in in aleppo i us to have my own tailor shop but i couldn t stand by and just watch peopl get injur in the street so i becam a volunt ambul driver you need to have a fearless heart to do my job becaus when you enter an area that s be bomb you take the risk of never come back aliv but peopl need my help and i want to do anyth i can to help them the feel i get from save live ha made me fearless befor the non stop bomb began i us to go to work drink a coffe with my colleagu and wait all dai for just on phone call nowadai we ar so overwhelm with injuri we can t distinguish between night and dai two dai ago i almost got kill twice i got a rescu call and wa head to al salheen neighbourhood when the regim hit the area with a doubl tap strike my ambul almost got hit by the bomb both time thank god i had the chanc to live anoth dai to see my famili recent i leav my home and my daughter alwai ask me to promis her that i ll come back home safe i sai goodby to her and my wife not know if i can keep thi promis no on can can promis anyon anyth these dai everyth can chang within a few second on bomb can chang your life forev when i transport the injur i alwai think that the person could easili be my friend my wife my daughter it could be anyon with all the bomb that s happen everi hour here it is too hard to save all of the the injur peopl i ve had a lot of situat where someon in my ambul is take hi or her last breath and there is noth i can do i keep drive search for the closest medic point but it s too hard to find on becaus the locat keep chang due to the bomb recent we haven t been abl to get fuel for our ambul almost all of the injur ar be taken to medic point by bicycl or wagon that ar normal us for sell veget it s a scene that cannot be describ peopl push bodi in a wagon cover in blood scream where is the nearest medic point pleas i need someon help me push someon help me find a doctor pleas he she is dy and suddenli the scream stop and the patient is lost it is almost imposs to take ani injur person to a medic point unless it s close by anyon who get injur by a medic point feel lucki as if thei have just won the lotteri the prize of life __label__angry

man interrupt him let him in he s a doctor i wish i had not been in that hospit yesterdai and that i did not see what i saw a sea of blood and the wound doctor and medic were swim in it i move through row of injur peopl all ly on the ground in a critic condit and each tri to muster some strength to motion to me with their hand or to whimper anyth that express their pain thei want to send me the messag i am wound and you have been chosen by god to rescu me or els to experi pain from your inabl to rescu me as i come to the realiz that we have all reach break point in that wretch hospit room a voic came down to us as if from abov we all listen attent to thi voic hope it will sai someth to calm us down the voic start gui empti the intens care unit the warplan ha launch a second strike and a third and and a tenth and i begin to see the injuri multipli the number of death multipli and i realiz there is no more blood for transfus no more sanit medic equip and no more serum bag but we continu work as if it s the end of the world even the wound look at you with the ey of those who have been condemn to hope and as soon as you re done with an injur civilian anoth look at you with plead ey that ar sai my fate depend on you as i m head toward on of the victim anoth on ly prostrat on the ground right next to him take hold of my arm and plead doctor i swear i wa here befor him i arriv right after the first strike and in that moment i wish i could be shatter into hundr of piec so that each piec could treat someon s brother or mother or father then my colleagu anoth doctor help treat the wound yell come check out my cousin i think he di but i can t make a final decis anoth on yell doctor come see thi gui that i tri to reviv i think he s dead other peopl stand around and ask that gui breath from hi neck is there anyth we can do to help him doctor is there anyth i can help you with i turn around and see an ophthalmologist who came from ghouta to share my burden and carri out the duti that god ha thrust upon him same with the pediatrician and same with the neurologist becaus thei see all the wound as famili syrian ar on peopl a few hour have elaps sinc the air raid and i now look across the intens care unit at least the ground ha been empti of it injur although the bed ar still all occupi i begin to feel that the situat is a bit more manag now thi is when the rescu oper end and the real catastroph begin the syria civil defens team have document more than death soul that have left thi life famili who have lost a member women who have lost a son a husband or a brother men who have lost a son a daughter a husband a father or a sibl i move through the oper room and see exhaust doctor who have perform more than surgeri dure the past few hour thei have seen gut spill out amput leg dislodg ey slash neck their green scrub ar dark from the blood as for those who have made it through the chaotic icu and surgeri thei ar look at dai or week at the hospit while
